cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.LG 

This paper deals with identifying heavy hitter flows in the data plane, which is a networking problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of hash tables and memory constraints, which are common topics in computer security (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also evaluates its algorithm using packet traces, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for heavy hitter detection, which could be considered as a machine learning problem (cs.LG).
